## Implementation Tips

### Start Small

Don't try to build all 5 playbooks at once. Start with **#1 (Threat Investigation)** because:
- It's the most common use case
- It provides immediate value
- It's relatively simple to build
- You can iterate and improve

### Use Parallel Processing

When building playbooks, use **parallel processing** for independent tasks:
- Query SIEM and EDR in parallel
- Check multiple threat intel feeds simultaneously
- Generate reports while collecting data

This can reduce playbook execution time by 60-80%.

### Validate Everything

Build validation into every playbook:
- Validate data before processing
- Check for errors at each step
- Ensure state consistency
- Log everything for audit

### Test Thoroughly

Test playbooks with:
- Real alerts (in a test environment)
- Edge cases (missing data, API failures)
- Performance (how long does it take?)
- Error handling (what happens when something fails?)

